3. STATION MENU

While docked at any space station you will have the following choice.

                              A. LEAVE STATION
                              B. NEWS
                              C. UPGRADES
                              D. MARKET
                              E. MILITARY
                              F. BULLETIN BOARD
                              G. SAVE POSITION
                              H. VIEW STARMAP

3a. LEAVE STATION

Lets you leave the station ready to fly to your next destination.


3b. NEWS

Depending on which station your at, you can read the latest news.
If your in Federation space you will hear their side of recent events such
as attacks by rebel or alien groups, or warnings of rebel activity in
particular star systems.

If your in Nodrog space you will hear their side of the story such as
unprovoked attacks by the Federation, or their attempts at trying to donate
items to the Federation.
You may even see your own name mentioned here if you've upset the Nodrogs
too many times.


3c. UPGRADES

If you have enough cash you can upgrade your ship with items like a bigger
cargo bay, fuel tank or a faster hyperdrive. Also there are combat and
defense upgrades such as stronger lasers, missiles, energy bombs and
shield boosters.
These are neccessary if you want to survive.


3d. MARKET

An essential stopping point at every station. The best way to make money is
to trade. Some systems import certain items while others export them.
So there is a good chance of making some serious cash.


3e. MILITARY

Again, depending on which station your at you will either meet the Federation
or the Nodrog Empire.
If it's the Nodrogs then they will ask you to leave and take a message to
the Federation. It isn't normally a nice message.

If you're in Federation space then you will be offered a mission.
The missions depend on your rank and experience. Initially, the missions
will be quite easy. They will always involve destroying rebel ships.
The first few missions will be to destroy up to 3 Pirate ships in various
systems. You will then progress to the Mafia, Saltire and eventually
the Nodrogs.
The Federation will tell you which system to travel to. Once there you
should be attacked by the rebels. They hang around the edge of the system
waiting for ships to arrive. Once destroyed, you will receive a message
from the Federation and payment.

The ships you will encounter will be quite easy to destroy but as you
progress you will come up against some tough ships so you will have to
spend your earnings on some decent combat equipment.

If you can't handle your current mission then goto the the Federation again,
you will be given the choice to keep going or abort.
It's up to you but the Federation only want fighters, not cowards.


3f. BULLETIN BOARD

This is another easy way to make some cash.

Now that the human race has spread through the galaxy it can take a while
for something to be delivered.
It's not a simple case of slapping a 1st class stamp on a parcel anymore.

People are still ordering items through mail order and are prepared to pay
some serious cash to get them.
The Universal Mail Co. rely on passing ships to deliver these items.
Payment depends on the distance of the system it's being sent to.

There will be a choice of five deliveries. Selecting any one of them will
tell you the location, the receiver and the item that is being delivered.
If you are going that way, press accept and the parcel is now yours.
Payment will be made once you arrive at any station in that system.
Once accepted, you will be taken back to the options. The one you have
accepted will now state "DELIVERY SECURED".

You can carry a maximum of three packages at any one time.


3g. SAVE POSITION

If it's late and your getting tired, select this option and choose a file
name. The data will be saved to enable you to continue another time.


3h. VIEW STARMAP

To see a map of the explored galaxy, press the mouse button on the large
window of the space station.

To use the map, move the mouse to the bottom of the screen. The map will
now scroll down. To scroll up, move the mouse to the top. Easy, eh!
A ring of dots will show which system you are currently in.

If the mouse moves over a star, the pointer will change. Pressing the right
mouse button on any star will show you a map of that system.

To exit the system map or the starmap, press either mouse button.


