5. THE COCKPIT

After leaving the station, you take control of your starship.
The top half of the screen is the cockpit window. The bottom half has the
controls.

                               A. SHIELDS
                               B. WEAPONS
                               C. SHIP
                               D. CAREER
                               E. MISSION
                               F. DATE
                               G. LOCAL MAP
                               H. STARMAP
                               I. HYPERWARP
                               J. DESTINATION

5a. SHIELDS

To the right od the controls, your shield strength will be shown. This starts
at 100% or higher depending on any boosters you may have.
This will be reduced in battle, so keep an eye on it. Once it gets to about
20% you had better get out of there.
To re-charge your shields, dock at any Federation space station.
They will automatically be re-charged.  


5b. WEAPONS

You can have up to three weapons, the laser, missiles and energy bomb.
When the mouse pointer is at the top half of the screen it will change to
the cross-hair to enable you to target enemy ships. Pressing the left mouse
button will fire the laser. The right mouse button will fire any missiles
you have.
If you have any missiles, they will be shown at the bottom left of the
cockpit.

To use the energy bomb, press the mouse button on the large blue star shaped
panel which is situated at the centre of the bottom half of the cockpit.
The engines will power up from red to yellow and release the bomb.
This sends out an energy wave, damaging any ships in the close vicinity.


5c. SHIP

This displays the equipment currently in use on your ship such as the
combat equipment, drive, cargo bay and fuel tank.
It will also show any cargo currently held.


5d. CAREER

This will show how well you're doing in the game. It displays;
Your rank, cash earned, years & months service, missions completed, total
amount of ships destoyed with individual amounts for the four enemies
and will also tell you your current combat rating.


5e. MISSION

If you forget were your going then look here. This will tell you who you
are after, where they are, how many there are and the payment on success.

It will also give the same details for any packages you have agreed to
deliver.


5f. DATE

Completely useless in space but relative to existence.


5g. LOCAL MAP

This is the map of the current system. Once selected, you can select any
of the space stations. You will then automatically head for that station.
After a while you will arrive at your destination and automatically dock
at the station. The time involved in travelling will depend upon the
number of enemy ships you encounter. Normally, it should take no longer
than a minute.


5h. STAR MAP

If you want to jump to another system then select this option.
It gives you a map of the occupied galaxy. Use the mouse to move the map up
and down by moving the pointer to the top and bottom of the screen.
A dotted ring will show your current system.
Once the mouse is on a star it will change to the cross-hair.

Pressing the left mouse button will select this star system and the dotted
ring will now surround the star.

Pressing the right mouse button will show the system map and give a
description. It will also tell you how much fuel is required to jump.

To get back to the cockpit, make sure the mouse is not on a star and press
either mouse button.
You will now be able to jump to the new system by selecting Hyperwarp.


5i. HYPERWARP

If you have selected a new system and have enough fuel, then you will jump
to the new system.


5j. DESTINATION

This will show where you're heading. If you have selected a space station to
fly to, then it will tell you which one.

