6. THE ENEMY

As mentioned before, there are four enemies of the Federation.
These are:

                               A. PIRATES
                               B. MAFIA
                               C. SALTIRE
                               D. NODROGS

6a. PIRATES

When you meet these chaps your monitor will show a skull and cross-bones.
Their ships are usually dull colours like grey and brown.
They are very common and you will meet them in most systems.
Usually they fly around in goups to maximise thier profit but now and
again some go alone.


6b. MAFIA

These folk are a bit more selective about the sytems they visit. They won't
go anywhere near Nodrog space but you will meet them everywhewre else.
Their call sign is a dark skull with blue eyes.
As with the Pirates, they have dull coloured ships. Their base is rumoured
to be the Procyon system so it would be advisable to avoid that area unless
you have some decent weapons.


6c. SALTIRE

This rebel group operate as a seperate race although they are human.
Their call sign is a white cross on a blue background,
No-one is sure why this is as no-one knows who they are or where they are
based.
They frequent the systems in the middle of the map but rarely venture into
Nodrog space. Their ships are only one colour. Blue.
There are rumours of an unmapped star sytem which the Saltire use as their
base but, as said before, no-one has any idea where it is.


6d. NODROGS

The Nodrogs occupy the last eight sytems at the top of the map. The homeworld
is Nodrog at the top-right of the map. Their logo is a golden "Z" with a
gold circle at either side.
They are not too fond of humans and often send insulting messages to their
targets.
The colour of their ships vary from orange, yellow, red and green. Often
they will mix a few colours.
You will not meet any Nodrogs unless you venture into their space. There are
reports of raids by the Nodrogs into Federation space but this is denied by
the Empire.


When engaged in combat, you should be able to tell how strong the enemy are
by the colour of the laser fire. The weakest is red with the strongest
being white. Usually, the ships shield strength is consistent with their
laser power. It's common sense really. Why bother spending so much money
on a strong laser if you don't strengthen your defense.

